European stock markets rose in initial trading on Tuesday, with London gaining ground after a long holiday weekend. In initial deals, the British capital's benchmark FTSE 100 index inched up 0.2% to 7 294.65 points, compared with the closing level on Friday. Subscribe to Fin24’s newsletter here In the eurozone, Frankfurt's DAX 30 also added 0.2% to 12 100.39 points and the Paris CAC 40 advanced 0.1% to 5 343.30 compared with Monday's close.